ths[right] = min(min_lengths[right - 1], current_length)\n            else:\n                min_lengths[right] = min_lengths[right - 1]\n        \n        return result if result < float('inf') else -1\n```\n\nThis solution uses a prefix sum array to efficiently calculate the sum of any sub-array. It maintains a sliding window approach to find sub-arrays with the target sum and keeps track of the minimum lengths of such sub-arrays. The `min_lengths` array helps in storing the minimum length of valid sub-array ending at each position, which is used to find the minimum sum of lengths of two non-overlapping sub-arrays.", "estimated_date": 1591488000000}